body.name: SideTrak Solo Pro 15.8" Portable Monitor - FHD 1080P LED Anti-Glare IPS Screen, Dual Display, for Mac, PC, Chrome Laptops, Game Consoles, USB or Mini HDMI Power, Double DisplayPort, Speakers, and HDR
features: Cutting-Edge Dual Screen Advantage - Instantly enhance your laptop workspace with this plug-and-play, freestanding portable monitor. Working with a dual screen setup boosts productivity, allowing more time for important tasks.

Stunning Picture Quality - Experience stunning visuals on this 15.8” Full HD LED IPS anti-glare dual screen monitor. Activate HDR Mode for gaming or movie streaming, ensuring a vibrant, true-to-life picture with low latency.
Sleek and Portable - This lightweight monitor boasts ultra-thin bezels for a seamless picture and a sleek, matte finish. Ideal for travel and on-the-go use.
Customizable Settings - Adjust brightness, volume, display settings, and screen orientation to your preference with ease.

Ultra Compatibility - This portable monitor, powered by Mini HDMI and USB-A or USB-C port, supports video streaming and power transmission to a wide range of devices and operating systems, including Mac, PC, and Chrome. Always check laptop ports before purchasing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great way to have a very portable 2nd display
reviews.reviewText: This is by far one of the most portable 2nd monitors I have ever used. Love it only has 1 cable and is very small/thin. Yes, I think it's a little expensive for a 2nd monitor but you can't beat how small/easy it is to use/bring/carry.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 10, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works perfectly with the MacBook Pro (15 inch, 2017) laptop.
reviews.reviewText: It was absolutely plug and play with the included USB-C to USB-C cable, and the screen resolution is about the same as with the MacBook Pro. (My laptop is a pre-Retina display.) And it draws its power from the laptop, meaning you don't need to have a power outlet somewhere to use the setup.I use it as a second screen when developing software, and the display is lightweight enough to pack and travel with when I want to get out of the house but still be able to get work done. The display can be made bright enough to work in a shaded outdoor environment--though when the brightness is turned all the way up and you're running intensive processes on the MacBook Pro, you can eat through the battery in just about three hours.It's perfect, and allows me to enjoy my back deck during the spring.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect Side Screen
reviews.reviewText: I got this screen to have an extra display when working off my laptop for you. I had first ordered a different version by the same company. However, I was not a fan of how small the screen was. I defiantly underestimated the scale of a 12-inch screen. So, I went and returned that one and then ordered this one. It was defiantly the better choice. The biggest down fall is the touch screen. Now the touch screen dose work well. It is just that being that it is not a Windows Surface or an Apple Tablet the computer gets confused some time. Those previously mentioned tablets are program to accept things like stylist pens and understand that when your pam in on the screen to ignore it and pay attention to the stylist. Now I do not know if this is an add on or a software update, they can make to the display. Like maybe if there is an option to select to only acknowledge a stylist pen and ignore other commands. However, if you do not plan to use a stylist pen then yes, the touch screen works perfectly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 12, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Picture and Performance
reviews.reviewText: Just received the non-touchscreen monitor today. My conputer has a Display Link connection, so I purchased a Display Link to HDMI adapter in advance. Since my USB-C port was not a display port, I had to connect the monitor to the computer via the adapter I bought and also plug in the USB-C to power the monitor. It connected instantly. Love that I can adjust the brightness and sharpness of the screen. Also like that it has volume. After making minor adjustments to the brightness and sharpness, I was all set to start using the monitor. The only complaint I have is that there is nothing to protect the screen. I have a slim, padded laptop case that I am putting it in for travel purposes since I plan to use this for work. Hence, there is a high probability that the screen can become damaged in transporting the monitor around. As such, I would recommend that SideTrack add some type of protective cover in the future. Until then, I reocmmend some type of protection plan or investing in a good carrying case. Overall, I am pleased with the purchase so far.

It was a bit on the pricier side and I’m not sure if the price is really worth it especially since my screen stopped working after some time and I had to order a replacement.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 7, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Don't expect Sidetrak Customer Service to respond to inquiries
reviews.reviewText: I was really looking forward to using these SideTrak touchscreen monitors to support my online training needs. Pricing was good, delivery was timely, packaging was neat – but I was not prepared for the technical difficulties and the lack of customer service support.Experienced no issues with the initial setup as side monitors using Dell laptop. Only have one USB-C port, so on one monitor, I am using the USB-C to USB-C cable (left), and a USB-C to USB-A PLUS Mini HDMI to HDMI cable for the other monitor (right). Installation instructions were easy to follow for the initial setup as side monitors.All aspects of these extended monitors are excellent (clarity, brightness, etc.) EXCEPT for the touch capability and audio... which is why I spent the extra money! When only one monitor is plugged in, the touchscreen works, but only after closing the large-tab Windows search icon. However, when plugging in a second monitor, BOTH monitors lose the touchscreen functionality, and all touchscreen activity reverts back to the main monitor. For example, when performing a screen highlight on the left or right monitor using a stylus, you can see the same area being highlighted on the pc monitor, not on either the left/right touchscreen monitor. In addition, when both monitors are attached, all audio playing from a video on one monitor plays to speakers on the opposite monitor (not to the PC).Nowhere (websites, support, etc.) does it indicate that only one Sidetrack will work at a time. There are only 3 troubleshooting questions answered on their website, none address these technical issues. I've verified and met technical requirements, tried various cabling combinations, read up on everything I could find on the Q&A, etc..There must be an easy fix, but I can’t seem to get a hold of SideTrak customer support. There is no Chat functionality for technical support. I’ve called 9 times during their normal business hours – after waiting 5 minutes each, receive a “call back during business hours” message. Submitted a form online to call me – and the response is that they are having technical issues with their phone system… still waiting for someone, anyone, to call me back.Do I really want to keep a product when not one person in technical support has a working phone that can return a call to resolve a technical issue during normal business hours?I’m rating this a “1” not based on the product itself, but on its Product Support (or lack thereof).
